## Goal

Generate 2–3 concrete approaches to the planned change, evaluate trade-offs, and commit to one recommendation.

## Steps

1. Load context: `memory_recall(topic_key="sdd-<change_id>-context")`
2. Generate 2–3 distinct approaches — include the obvious path and at least one alternative
3. For each approach evaluate: implementation complexity, reversibility, blast radius, testability
4. Select the recommended approach with a clear rationale
5. Save to memory:
   - title: `SDD Proposal: <change_id>`
   - topic_key: `sdd-<change_id>-proposal`
   - type: `decision`
   - content (structured):
     ```
     ## Approach A: <name>
     <description, pros, cons>

     ## Approach B: <name>
     <description, pros, cons>

     ## Approach C: <name> (if applicable)
     <description, pros, cons>

     ## Recommended: <Approach X>
     <rationale — why this one, why not the others>
     ```

## Constraints

- No implementation code in this phase
- Each approach must be genuinely distinct (not variations of the same idea)
- The recommendation must be unambiguous — one winner

## Board Update

**After saving to memory**, update the project board. Check your prompt for an issue number (look for `for issue #N` or `#<number>`). If found, execute the commands below with `<ISSUE_NUMBER>` replaced by that number. **If no issue number is present in your prompt, skip this entire section.**

```bash
ITEM_ID=$(gh api graphql -f query='query{organization(login:"reverberage"){projectV2(number:2){items(first:100){nodes{id content{...on Issue{number}}}}}}}' --jq '.data.organization.projectV2.items.nodes[] | select(.content.number == <ISSUE_NUMBER>) | .id')
[ -n "$ITEM_ID" ] && gh project item-edit --id "$ITEM_ID" --field-id PVTSSF_lADOEeFGTc4Bc5CtzhXejII --project-id PVT_kwDOEeFGTc4Bc5Ct --single-select-option-id 47fc9ee4
[ -n "$ITEM_ID" ] && gh project item-edit --id "$ITEM_ID" --field-id PVTSSF_lADOEeFGTc4Bc5CtzhYUpaI --project-id PVT_kwDOEeFGTc4Bc5Ct --single-select-option-id f7b5e3ad
```
